<h4>What the AI Conversion Looks Like</h4>
<p>For each React component, the AI does three things:</p>
<ol>
    <li><b>Strips React syntax</b> &mdash; removes <code>useState</code>, <code>useEffect</code>, JSX &rarr; standard HTML, TypeScript types removed</li>
    <li><b>Keeps everything else</b> &mdash; CSS classes, HTML structure, colour values, scoring formulas, filter logic</li>
    <li><b>Swaps data source</b> &mdash; <code>localStorage.getItem()</code> &rarr; <code>fetch("/_api/cr_aiideas")</code></li>
</ol>

<h4>Example: Data Layer Change (the only real code change)</h4>
<div class="callout">
<code>// BEFORE (React/TypeScript &mdash; ideaService.ts)<br/>
const ideas = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('advisory_ai_ideas'));<br/><br/>
// AFTER (Power Pages &mdash; vanilla JavaScript)<br/>
async function getIdeas() {<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;const res = await fetch("/_api/cr_aiideas?$orderby=cr_createdat desc");<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;return (await res.json()).value;<br/>
}<br/>
async function submitIdea(idea) {<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;await fetch("/_api/cr_aiideas", {<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;method: "POST",<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;body: JSON.stringify(idea)<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;});<br/>
}</code>
</div>

<h4>Scoring Logic: Unchanged</h4>
<div class="callout">
<code>// Same function, just remove TypeScript type annotations<br/>
const scoreValues = { low: 1, medium: 2, high: 3 };<br/><br/>
function calculateValueScore(a) {<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;return scoreValues[a.businessGrowth] * 0.20<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ scoreValues[a.costEfficiency] * 0.20<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ scoreValues[a.businessResilience] * 0.30<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;+ scoreValues[a.businessAgility] * 0.30;<br/>
}<br/>
function determineQuadrant(val, feas) {<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (val >= 2 &amp;&amp; feas >= 2) return "Likely Wins";<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (val >= 2 &amp;&amp; feas &lt; 2) return "Calculated Risks";<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;if (val &lt; 2 &amp;&amp; feas >= 2) return "Marginal Gains";<br/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;return "Avoid";<br/>
}</code>
</div>

